HEADWORD: Chaeronea
<hw>Chaeronea</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Greek antiquity)</fld>
<def>either of two battles in ancient Greece, one in which Philip of
Macedon defeated the Athenians and Thebans (338 BC), or another in which
Sulla defeated Mithridates (86 BC).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

